Yes. We went to Sunday school. And further more - there used to be - a carter's mission, a carter's that was run by carters. In spring Lane. At Spring Lane in - the - off - off of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
Street}}Shamrock Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Off of - off of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Wellington Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And - you got - cake, you got a cup of tea - and on a Saturday night you got a cup of tea and - and cake. And I think it was a penny. For a penny or something like that. And my mother saw that we were there that every Saturday night. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9049349 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13703802\charrsid1209268 What sort of things did you used to do there?
